  "timeline": [
    "1950s–1960s: Early foundations with Management Information Systems (MIS) focusing on automation and efficiency.",
    "1970s: Birth of socio-technical systems theory emphasizing joint design of technology and social systems.",
    "1980s: Human-Centered and Participatory Design movements emerge, leading to co-design with users.",
    "1985–1995: Computer-Supported Cooperative Work (CSCW) and Organizational Informatics are formalized as research fields.",
    "Late 1990s: Shift to studying information infrastructures, with concepts like invisible work and boundary objects.",
    "2000s: Massive adoption of ERP systems and globalization, leading to focus on organizational change and user resistance.",
    "2010s: Rise of platforms, mobility, and datafication, making digital labor and data ethics central concerns.",
    "2020s: COVID-19 accelerates remote work and digital transformation, focusing research on hybrid collaboration and AI systems."
  ],
